## Phase 2: Computed Attribute Integration

### 2.1 Add expressionType to ProfileAttributeConfig

File: src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/entity/ProfileAttributeConfig.java

Add field:
  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
  @Column(name = "expression_type", length = 10)
  private ExpressionType expressionType = ExpressionType.TEMPLATE;

### 2.2 Create ExpressionType enum

File: src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/entity/enums/ExpressionType.java

public enum ExpressionType {
    TEMPLATE,   // existing ${attr} interpolation (default, backward compatible)
    SCRIPT      // GraalJS evaluation
}

### 2.3 Flyway migration

File: src/main/resources/db/migration/V<next>__add_expression_type.sql

ALTER TABLE profile_attribute_configs
    ADD COLUMN expression_type VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'TEMPLATE';

No data migration needed — all existing rows get TEMPLATE default.

### 2.4 Update ProvisioningProfileService.applyDefaults()

File: src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/service/ProvisioningProfileService.java

In the computed expression block (~line 486-493), branch on expressionType:

  if (config.getExpressionType() == ExpressionType.SCRIPT) {
      // Build bindings: flatten attributes map (first values) into a "ctx" object
      Map<String, Object> ctx = new LinkedHashMap<>();
      attributes.forEach((k, v) -> ctx.put(k, (v != null && !v.isEmpty()) ? v.get(0) : ""));
      Map<String, Object> bindings = Map.of("ctx", ctx);
      String computed = scriptService.evaluateToString(config.getComputedExpression(), bindings);
      if (computed != null && !computed.isBlank()) {
          attributes.put(config.getAttributeName(), List.of(computed));
          continue;
      }
  } else {
      // existing evaluateExpression() call — unchanged
  }

Inject ScriptEvaluationService into ProvisioningProfileService.

### 2.5 Update DTOs

Files:
  - src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/dto/profile/CreateProfileRequest.java
  - src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/dto/profile/ProfileResponse.java

Add `expressionType` field (String) to AttributeConfigEntry records in both.
Default to "TEMPLATE" when null/absent for backward compatibility.

### 2.6 Update profile save logic

File: src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/service/ProvisioningProfileService.java

In the method that maps DTO → entity (where AttributeConfigEntry is persisted),
set config.setExpressionType() from the DTO value. Parse string to enum, default TEMPLATE.

