## Phase 3: Playbook Script Step

### 3.1 Add SCRIPT action to PlaybookStepAction enum

File: src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/entity/enums/PlaybookStepAction.java

Add:  SCRIPT

### 3.2 Implement SCRIPT case in executeStep()

File: src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/service/LifecyclePlaybookService.java

In the switch statement in executeStep() (~line 290), add:

  case SCRIPT -> {
      String scriptBody = params.path("script").asText();

      // Build rich context for the script
      LdapUser user = ldapUserService.getUser(dc, targetDn);
      Map<String, Object> ctx = new LinkedHashMap<>();
      ctx.put("dn", targetDn);
      ctx.put("directoryId", dc.getId().toString());
      ctx.put("attributes", user.getAttributes());  // Map<String, List<String>>

      Map<String, Object> bindings = Map.of("ctx", ctx, "result", new LinkedHashMap<>());
      Map<String, Object> result = scriptService.evaluateToMap(scriptBody, bindings);

      // Interpret result actions
      applyScriptResult(dc, targetDn, result);
  }

Inject ScriptEvaluationService into LifecyclePlaybookService.

### 3.3 Create applyScriptResult() helper

File: src/main/java/com/ldapadmin/service/LifecyclePlaybookService.java

Private method that reads the result map and dispatches actions:

  private void applyScriptResult(DirectoryConnection dc, String targetDn, Map<String, Object> result) {
      // result.action — optional: "DISABLE", "ENABLE", "DELETE", "MOVE_OU"
      // result.targetDn — for MOVE_OU
      // result.setAttributes — Map<String, String> of attributes to set
      // result.removeAttributes — List<String> of attributes to remove
      // result.addGroups — List<String> of group DNs to add to
      // result.removeGroups — List<String> of group DNs to remove from
  }

Each key is optional. If result is empty/null, the step is a no-op (useful for
scripts that only compute values for subsequent steps or log decisions).

### 3.4 Rollback for SCRIPT steps

In the rollback switch statement (~line 225-272), SCRIPT steps are treated as
non-reversible (same as DELETE/NOTIFY):

  case SCRIPT -> log.warn("Cannot auto-rollback SCRIPT step {} for {}", step, targetDn);

This is the safe default. Scripts that only set attributes will have their
previous state captured by capturePreviousState(), but the composite nature
of script results makes automatic rollback unreliable.

### 3.5 Preview for SCRIPT steps

In the preview logic, SCRIPT steps show:
  description: "Run script"  (or first line/comment of script body)
  reversible: false

### 3.6 Update DTOs

No DTO changes needed — the existing `parameters` JSON field carries the script:
  { "script": "if (ctx.attributes.department[0] === ...) { ... }" }

