## Phase 4: Security Hardening

### 4.1 Script size limit

In ScriptEvaluationService.evaluate(), reject scripts exceeding a configurable
max length (default 50_000 chars). Prevents memory abuse.

### 4.2 Feature-gate script creation

Only SUPERADMIN can create/edit attributes with expressionType=SCRIPT or
playbook steps with action=SCRIPT. Enforce in:
  - ProvisioningProfileService (profile save validation)
  - LifecyclePlaybookService (playbook create/update validation)

This prevents regular admins from injecting arbitrary code.

### 4.3 Audit logging

Log all script executions to the audit trail:
  - AuditAction.SCRIPT_EXECUTED
  - Include: script hash (not full source), execution time, success/failure, caller context

### 4.4 Resource limits

Configure in the GraalJS Context:
  - option("engine.MaximumStackDepth", "100")  — prevent stack overflow
  - Statement limit via ResourceLimits (if available in version)
  - Already sandboxed: no I/O, no threads, no native access, no host access

